      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Manners let HI MANAMEISJEFF NZ (8) down as a hot favourite last start but he had won two in row prior including the Group 2 Light Horse FFA from a similar draw to this. Has a terrific record at this circuit and distance, winning 12 of 17. Jye Coney goes aboard having won his two drives on him. He can get back on track if he behaves. CHASE A DREAM NZ (6) has been good from wide barriers in his last two outings, particularly two back when he raced three wide without cover but dug deep to miss by a nose. Draws lower and Hart drives him over Hi Manameisjeff. He'll go close if he performs up to his close second to Leap To Fame at this circuit and distance in March. PINSEEKER NZ (2) worked and faded last start but overcame a wide draw and beat Chase A Dream to win here prior. Well served by the draw as is JILLIBY NITRO (1) who has been racing very well with a string of wins and placings from wider or second row barriers. CAPTAIN BELLASARIO (3) must be respected after winning from wider last week.",
